  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7100.5 sitting right between the negative gamma pocket at 7115 (-4834M) and positive gamma support at 7100 (+4832M), dealers are likely buying this dip given the PIN regime and wall break event. The strong positive gamma walls at 7150 (+5883M) and especially 7200 (+7462M) should act as magnets and resistance, with dealers selling into any rally toward those levels. Key levels to watch: 7115 for potential amplification if we break higher, and 7200 as the major dealer selling zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce toward 7150-7200 where selling pressure kicks in.",
